During adipogenesis, is rapidly expressed and, after activation by phosphorylation, induces CEBPA and PPARG, which turn on the series of adipocyte genes that give rise to the adipocyte phenotype. Essential for female reproduction because of a critical role in ovarian follicle development (By similarity).
